    <item>
      <title>BTK</title>
      <link>/genepanel/695/info/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 05 May 2019 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>/genepanel/695/info/</guid>
      <description>


&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bruton tyrosine kinase&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p align=&#34;left&#34; style=&#34;font-size:16px&#34;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ENTREZID: &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/695&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;695&lt;/a&gt; | Type: Protein Coding |
Map: &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/genome/gdv/browser/gene/?id=695&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt; Xq22.1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
OMIM: &lt;a href=&#39;https://omim.org/entry/307200&#39; target=&#39;_blank&#39;&gt;307200&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&#39;https://omim.org/entry/300755&#39; target=&#39;_blank&#39;&gt;300755&lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&#39;https://omim.org/entry/300300&#39; target=&#39;_blank&#39;&gt;300300&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p align=&#34;justify&#34; style=&#34;font-size:16px&#34;&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Summary Entrez&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;The protein encoded by this gene plays a crucial role in B-cell development. Mutations in this gene cause X-linked agammaglobulinemia type 1, which is an immunodeficiency characterized by the failure to produce mature B lymphocytes, and associated with a failure of Ig heavy chain rearrangement. Alternative splicing results in multiple transcript variants encoding different isoforms. [provided by RefSeq, Dec 2013] &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
</description>
